{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish Care Charter to guarantee acceptable standards for Health & Homecare.",
        "additional_details": "For the patient & family to be treated with dignity and respect in their own home\r\n\r\nProvider should be CQC checked & cleared before providing any care\r\n\r\nAppropriate care:  Complex care needs requiring Healthcare not Homecare provision\r\n\r\nNo immediate withdrawal of care without proper consultation or a satisfactory replacement being agreed. Provider to follow own T&C's \r\n\r\nNo single carer when there is a statutory requirement for double-handled care\r\n\r\nTo meet statutory requirements for arrival times \r\n\r\nTo provide point of contact to reasonably discuss issues and to contact clients when problems arise\r\n\r\nMy late mother, Mrs Judith Lanceley received unacceptable care. Establishing a Care Charter in her name, to help others, as part of her legacy\r\n\r\nThank you for your support",
        "background": "The Government should legislate for a Care Charter to guarantee that those being cared for by Health & Homecare Agencies are treated appropriately and safely at all times.\r\n\r\nThe Charter should include:",
